The paper is about the Shapley value, a central concept in cooperative game theory, and its computation using sampling-based approximation methods. This topic falls under the category of computational game theory, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that deals with the algorithmic and computational aspects of game theory. Specifically, the paper focuses on the efficiency and accuracy of sampling-based approximation methods for computing the Shapley value, which is a problem of interest in machine learning, artificial intelligence, and data science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.GT (Computational Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
